serverSide.sharedRegions

Class Table

  • java.lang.Object
    • serverSide.sharedRegions.Table

  • public class Table
extends java.lang.Object
    Table. It is responsible to keep a continuously updated account of the Students inside the Table and is implemented as an implicit monitor. All public methods are executed in mutual exclusion. There are two internal synchronization points: a single blocking point for the barbers, where they wait for a Student; and an array of blocking points, one per each Student, where he both waits his turn to cut the hair and sits on the cutting chair while having his hair cut.
